cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark or its evaluation set, please cite it as below."
title: "FBC Model-Routing Benchmark: LLM citation accuracy on the Florida Building Code, cold vs. grounded"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Lopez"
    given-names: "Yadel"
repository-code: "https://github.com/dotnetspark/fbc-model-routing-benchmark"
license: MIT
date-released: "2026-07-17"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible benchmark of model-routing decisions on a deterministically
  checkable task: whether an LLM cites the section of the Florida Building Code
  (and Naples/Collier County local amendments) that the published code assigns.
  Three model tiers, cold vs. grounded, scored by regex citation match against
  gold sections verified against primary sources.
